StmtSimple.@StatementText:
CREATE procedure [dbo].[stat_change_instruct]
@t_testing_id uniqueidentifier

as 
declare @status varchar(10) 
declare @t_test_id uniqueidentifier
declare @step_order int
declare @current_step_id uniqueidentifier

SET XACT_ABORT ON;

select @status=obj_name from t_testing_status ts
inner join t_testing t on ts.t_testing_status_id = t.t_testing_status_id
where  t.t_testing_id = @t_testing_id

begin
  
  select @t_test_id=t_test_id
  
  from   t_test
  where order_num =
  (
  select min(order_num) 
  from t_testing_test tt inner join t_test te
    on tt.t_test_id= te.t_test_id
    where tt.t_testing_test_status_id = 4
    and tt.t_testing_id = @t_testing_id
  )

update  t_testing 
  set t_testing_status_id = 1,
  current_test_id = @t_test_id
  where t_testing_id = @t_testing_id

ScalarOperator.@ScalarString: CASE WHEN [Expr1017] IS NULL THEN (0) ELSE CASE WHEN NOT [Pass1019] AND [Expr1018] IS NULL THEN (1) ELSE NULL END END

StmtSimple.@StatementText:
select @current_step_id= t_test_step_id
  from t_test_step
  where t_test_id=@t_test_id 
  and step_order=@step_order

update t_testing_test
  set current_step_id=@current_step_id,
  t_testing_test_status_id=1
  where t_testing_id = @t_testing_id
  and t_test_id=@t_test_id

ScalarOperator.@ScalarString: CASE WHEN [Expr1016] IS NULL THEN (0) ELSE NULL END

StmtSimple.@StatementText:
update  
  t_testing_step 
  set 
  t_testing_step_status_id = 1,
  view_date=getdate()
  where t_test_step_id=@current_step_id
    and t_testing_id = @t_testing_id

ScalarOperator.@ScalarString: CASE WHEN [Expr1018] IS NULL THEN (0) ELSE NULL END

StmtSimple.@StatementText:
update  t_testing
  set start_date=getdate()
  where t_testing_id = @t_testing_id
  and start_date is null
